<html><head><title>DiscomBobulation</title></head><body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<table width=100%><tr><td align=left valign=top><img src="../images/am.gif" width="258" height="26" alt="American Survey" border=0>
<td align=right valign=top><img src="http://www.economist.com/econlogosmall.gif" width="78" height="39" alt="The Economist" border=0></td></tr></table>


<table border=6><tr><td><h1>DiscomBobulation</h1>

<font size=1>WASHINGTON, DC</font><p><b>
WAS the 1996 campaign really so boring? We think not. Dole-speak, provided liberally (as it were) by the Republican candidate, gave delight and bafflement in equal measure. Here, nostalgically, is a parting selection:</b><p><br>
We've had millions and millions of dollars spent in Florida saying Bob Dole is against Medicare, Bob Dole is against Social Security, Bob Dole is against veterans, Bob Dole is against children. There<i>'</i>s nobody left. I<i>'</i>m against everybody.<br>
<i>St Petersburg, Florida, September 9th</i><p>[Clinton] came out against truancy, which I thought was courageous, said he's opposed to it. And I said, <i>'</i>'That's . . .that's statesmanship." Didn<i>'</i>t even take a poll. He just did it on his own.<br>
<i>Springfield, Virginia, September 23rd</i><p>
The cause of crime can be explained with one simple word: criminals, criminals, criminals.<br>
<i>Philadelphia, September 16th</i><p>They [the Clinton administration] look you in the eye and say<i>, </i>we're going to give you targeted tax cuts if you keep your room clean and eat your vegetables and do all the other things the government wants you to do. And if you eat your vegetables, you could live as long as Senator Thurmond, who is going to be re-elected without any problems. I used to follow him around. When he ate a banana, I ate a banana. Whatever worked.<i><br>
Irvine, California, October 29th</i><p>I will dedicate my presidency to restoring the clarity with which our government speaks.<br>
<i>Philadelphia,September 16th</i><br>
</tr></table>


