<html><head><title>Britain In Brief</title></head><body bgcolor="#ffffff">
<center><p align=center>
<table width=65% align=center><tr><td valign=top align=center>
<img src="http://www.economist.com/econlogosmall.gif" width="78" height="39" alt="The Economist" border=0>
</p></center>
<p align=center><img src="../images/brbrief.gif" width="231" height="24" alt="Britain in Brief" border=0></p>
<p align=center><font size=-1>
These articles in the Britain section are published in the UK printed edition only, and are published here for the benefit of readers of non-UK editions.
</font></p></td></tr></table></center>

<hr size=6 align=center width=65%>
<center><table width=65%><tr valign=top><td valign=top width=30%>
 
<p><b>Warning shots</b> &nbsp; Prisoners belonging to the Ulster Defence Association, a loyalist paramilitary group, ended their support for the Northern Ireland peace effort, saying that the British government had failed to reward them for supporting the loyalist ceasefire in the face of renewed <font size=-1>IRA</font> violence. The British army blew up a car bomb in Belfast which was thought to have been planted by a republican splinter group. <br>
<p><b>Smoked</b> &nbsp; The lawyers for 40 people suffering from lung cancer agreed to bear up to &#163;3m of legal costs on a "no win, no fee" basis so that the victims could afford to sue two tobacco firms.<br>
<p><b>Gassed</b> &nbsp; British Gas suspended all disconnections after a new &#163;150m computer system caused chaos in its billing offices. Thousands of customers were sent letters saying they faced being cut off for non-payment, even though they had yet to receive their bills.<br>
</td><td width=5%></td><td valign=top width=30%>
<p><b>Regulation time</b> &nbsp; British Gas asked the Monopolies and Mergers Commission to investigate price limits proposed by Ofgas, the gas-industry regulator. Offer, the electricity regulator, confirmed plans to impose tough new price limits on the National Grid.<br>
<p><b>TV news</b> &nbsp; The <font size=-1>BBC</font> entered exclusive talks on launching its first subscription channels with two broadcasting firms part-owned by <font size=-1>TCI</font>, America's largest cable-television operator.<br>
<p><b>Inspectors call</b> &nbsp; The Serious Fraud Office raided the home of Peter Young, a fund manager sacked by Deutsche Morgan Grenfell, an investment bank, following allegations that three of its funds had been mismanaged.<br>
<p><b>Lost</b> &nbsp; Mandy Allwood lost all of her babies. She was expecting octuplets and rejected doctors' advice to abort some of the foetuses to try to save the others.<br>
<p><b>Eureka!</b> &nbsp; Ken Zetie of Oxford University won an award from the Institute of Physics for a paper debunking the widely believed idea that scientists had "proved" that it was impossible for bumblebees to fly.<br>

</td></tr></table></center>

