<hr size=6 align=center width=65%>
<center><table width=65%><tr valign=top><td valign=top width=30%>

<p><b>Talks</b> &nbsp; A meeting between Gerry Adams, president of Sinn Fein, and Jeremy Corbyn and Tony Benn, two Labour <font size=-1>MP</font>s, was moved to a venue outside the Palace of Westminster after Mr Corbyn was threatened with expulsion from the parliamentary Labour party if he met Mr Adams in the Commons.<br>
<p><b>Anti-Eurovision</b> &nbsp; The Referendum Party, a Eurosceptic group led by Sir James Goldsmith, a business tycoon, was granted the right to political broadcasts on television and radio during the next general election campaign.<br>
<p><b>Cybercensors</b> &nbsp; The government approved a new self-regulation system for Internet providers, to censor child pornography and other illegal material.<br>
<p><b>Stalkers stalked</b> &nbsp; The judge in the case of a man found guilty of continually following and threatening a 20 year-old woman said "stalking" should be made a criminal offence. Michael Howard, the home secretary, said he hoped such a law would be passed in the forthcoming session of Parliament.<br>
</td><td width=5%></td><td valign=top width=30%>
<p><b>In the clear</b> &nbsp; The Police Complaints Authority cleared Gloucester police of allegations made by a newspaper that some of their officers had used the home of serial killers Frederick and Rosemary West as a brothel.<br>
<p><b>Offshore haven</b> &nbsp; The parliament of Jersey passed a law allowing the formation of limited-liability partnerships--a move expected to lead accountancy firms to move their headquarters to the island so that their partners can avoid being sued over auditing errors.<br>
<p><b>Revelations</b> &nbsp; It emerged that Roderick Wright, who resigned as Roman Catholic bishop of Argyll and the Isles after running away with a divorc<e-acute>e, has a 15-year-old son by another woman. He caused further outrage by selling his story to the <i>News of the World</i>.<br>
<p><b>Wrong number</b> &nbsp; Essex County Council was criticised for spending &#163;7,000 on the registration number <font size=-1>ECC1</font> for one of its official limousines, when it is cutting its budget by up to &#163;75m.<br>

</td></tr></table></center>

